V2 coverage path further.\n\nChanged:\n- `tests/src/jdom/jdom/1.0b8/src/test/java/oracle/xml/parser/v2/DOMParser.java`\n  - Added explicit public overrides for:\n    - `parse(InputSource)`\n    - `getDocument()`\n\nWhy:\n- `OracleV2DOMAdapter.getDocument(...)` performs reflective lookup on `oracle.xml.parser.v2.DOMParser`.\n- Previously the fake Oracle V2 parser inherited these methods from `oracle.xml.parser.XMLParser`, which can make metadata/coverage attribution less direct for `DOMParser`.\n- Declaring the methods directly on `oracle.xml.parser.v2.DOMParser` makes the reflective `getMethod(...)` and `Method.invoke(...)` path target the same class that `OracleV2DOMAdapter` loads with `Class.forName(...)`.\n\nAlso retained the earlier fix:\n- The isolated callable now invokes `OracleV2DOMAdapter.getDocument(...)` directly and no longer calls a private helper across class loaders.\n\nI did not run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e48d08df9e3432d0169fc82d7f568819498817c0804906e62\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2798, "output": 475, "cacheRead": 42496, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45769, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778156240988, "responseId": "resp_0e48d08df9e3432d0169fc82d1941481948f4f81fc48194df9"}}
